AI Code Review Iteration1 Readability: Documentation Quality SeverityLow The constraint "2-10 minutes" for `traceDurationWindowInSeconds` is inconsistent with the valid values "120-600 seconds". The calculation shows 120 seconds equals 2 minutes and 600 seconds equals 10 minutes, which are correct, but mixing units creates potential confusion. It might be better to express both in the same unit (e.g., "120-600 seconds (2-10 minutes)"). Here is the suggested code: ```suggestion | `traceDurationWindowInSeconds` | Time window for trace aggregation | 120-600 seconds (2-10 minutes) | Required | ``` This comment refers to line 34 in the new file.
